title: Bug 10593: Jar export should add ".jar" suffix if not specified
OB: When exporting files using the jar export feature, if a file name is provided without a ".jar" suffix, the exported jar file is created with the provided name but without the ".jar" suffix.
EB: After selecting some files and exporting them using the jar export feature, if a file name is provided without a ".jar" suffix, the exported jar file should be created with the provided name including the ".jar" suffix.
SR: To reproduce this issue, select some files and export them using the jar export feature. Enter a file name without the ".jar" suffix as the jar name. Currently, the exported jar file will be created without the ".jar" suffix. The expected behavior is that the exported jar file should be created with the provided name including the ".jar" suffix.
